    "created_at": "2015-10-06T05:07:11Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-10-06T05:07:11Z",
    "body": "After some investigation, we do have a reliable source for extracting form request data and whole other information using the `WebFrame::provisionalDataSource` in `WillSubmitForm` event. But the problem we need to solve in our current architecture is how to pass one webframes' datasource to another newly created frame.\nOne solution is to set the opener of a frame in native side and during `LoadURL` first give renderer a chance for navigation (if it has POST data).\n- guest.LoadURL\n- Send IPC to renderer to give chance for POST navigation\n- Get the opener of the frame and check if it has POST dataSource\n- Use `WebFrame::Load` to navigate and return IPC result whether to continue browser navigation.\n\nAny other implementaion ideas ?\n"
  },
