    "created_at": "2015-10-06T16:42:10Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-10-06T16:42:10Z",
    "body": "Initially statrted with this approach but there was a problem with handling POST data on browser side is, a `WebHTTPBody` gets [constructed](https://code.google.com/p/chromium/codesearch#chromium/src/content/renderer/render_frame_impl.cc&sq=package:chromium&l=4687&rcl=1444131269) for navigation request and it has a few different [types of data](https://code.google.com/p/chromium/codesearch#chromium/src/third_party/WebKit/public/platform/WebHTTPBody.h&sq=package:chromium&l=52&rcl=1444131269), currently `LoadURLParams.browser_initiated_post_data` are extracted into only one type [here](https://code.google.com/p/chromium/codesearch#chromium/src/content/browser/frame_host/navigation_entry_impl.cc&l=460&cl=GROK&gsn=ConstructCommonNavigationParams), this might be problem for file upload. So we might need to patch chromium to change the type of `browser_initiated_post_data` similar to the one in this quite old but relevant [CL](https://codereview.chromium.org/11193051/) which tries to handle cross process POST navigations. If patching the type is fine then can proceed with your suggestion.\n"
  },
