      "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/zcbenz/events{/privacy}",
      "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/zcbenz/received_events",
      "type": "User",
      "site_admin": true
    },
    "created_at": "2015-10-08T04:15:01Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-10-08T04:15:01Z",
    "body": "Patching Chromium is not an one-off job, we have to maintain the patch when upgrading Chromium in future and it is not an easy work, so generally we should only patch Chromium when it is an urgent issue, or requested by many users. I think this issue may not deserver all the work for now.\n\nA more maintainable way to fix this is to propose the patch to upstream Chromium and wait them to merge it, and then fix the problem in Electron.\n"
  },
